fields.name: Apple Lightning- Type C
fields.description:
A Lighting-to-C charger is a cable that allows you to charge an iPhone or other Apple device with a USB-C charger. This can be useful if you have a newer laptop or power bank that only has USB-C ports.

Lighting-to-C chargers are available from a variety of manufacturers, including Apple. It is important to choose a charger that is certified by Apple to ensure that it will work safely and reliably with your device.

fields.name: Apple MagSafe
fields.description:
MagSafe is a wireless charging technology developed by Apple. It uses magnets to align the charger with the iPhone, ensuring that it is always in the optimal position for charging. MagSafe chargers can deliver up to 15W of power, which is faster than traditional wireless chargers.

MagSafe chargers are also compatible with MagSafe cases and accessories. This means that you can charge your iPhone without having to remove it from its case, and you can also use MagSafe accessories to attach your iPhone to other devices, such as a car mount or a MagSafe battery pack.
